tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE trading_log (
  signal_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  signal_datetime TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  signal_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  action_taken VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  algorithm_used VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  effectiveness DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE trading_signals (
    signal_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    symbol VARCHAR(255),
    signal_type VARCHAR(50),
    confidence_score FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE trading_actions (
    action_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    symbol VARCHAR(255),
    action_type VARCHAR(50),
    quantity INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE trading_signals (
    signal_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    signal_type VARCHAR(50),
    symbol VARCHAR(10),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    confidence_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE trading_actions (
    action_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    signal_id INT,
    action_type VARCHAR(50),
    executed_price FLOAT,
    executed_quantity INT,
    executed_timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE model_evaluations (
    evaluation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    evaluation_date DATE,
    evaluation_result VARCHAR(100),
    evaluation_notes TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE trading_signals (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    signal_type VARCHAR(50),
    asset_symbol VARCHAR(10),
    signal_strength FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE trading_actions (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    action_type VARCHAR(50),
    asset_symbol VARCHAR(10),
    quantity INT,
    price DECIMAL(10, 2),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE performance_metrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT,
    f1_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE evaluation_logs (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    signal_id INT,
    action_id INT,
    algorithm_id INT,
    result VARCHAR(255),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);
